      "_id": "page.future-resources---content",
      "_type": "content",
      "html": "## Online resources ##\r\nYou will find more information about fixing housing disrepair issues on these websites. \r\n\r\n- [Advice Now](https://www.advicenow.org.uk/guides/how-fix-problems-your-privately-rented-home)\r\n\r\n- [Shelter](https://england.shelter.org.uk/housing_advice/repairs)\r\n\r\n- [Citizens Advice](https://www.citizensadvice.org.uk/housing/repairs-in-rented-housing/)"
    },
    {
      "$component": true,
      "$content": true,
      "$definition": true,
      "_id": "page.future-resources---content--6",
      "_type": "content",
      "html": "## Consider organising the repair work yourself ##\r\n\r\nIf the problem is relatively small, you could arrange for the repairs to be done and take the cost out of your rent. However, it's important to keep your landlord informed, and follow a step-by-step process. You must not stop paying rent without notice. \r\n\r\nFind out more about [organising repairs yourself](https://england.shelter.org.uk/housing_advice/repairs/doing_the_repairs_if_your_landlord_wont) on the Shelter website. ",
